                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/393a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<gloss type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </gloss>)<note n="24" xml:id="d246fn1">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, to the Ambassador in France as No. 790, and to the
                        Ambassador in Russia as No. 315.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-06T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1915—7 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1519. Please call at the Foreign Office and inform the Government that we are
                    both alarmed and distressed at the news from Japan and China. Ask whether the
                    British Government will join us in a friendly but earnest appeal to Japan and
                    China to continue their negotiations in the spirit of patience and friendship
                    until a satisfactory conclusion is reached, representing that it would be
                    unfortunate beyond expression if these nations should be drawn into armed
                    conflict; and that as a friend of both nations we feel it our duty to ask the
                    cooperation of other friendly nations in an effort to prevent such a calamity. A
                    similar message is being sent to France and Russia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
